        <updateDate>2011-01-31T16:33:30Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Constitutional Amendment - Prohibits outlays for a fiscal year (except those for repayment of debt principal) from exceeding one-fifth of economic output of the United States, unless two-thirds of each chamber provide for a specific increase of outlays above this amount.</p> <p> <p> <p> <p>Authorizes waivers of these provisions when a declaration of war is in effect.]]></text>
      </summary>
